track_notes:
Free parking off highway TF-38 available if you come early. This lot fills up quickly! Most tourists do not stay long and you might have to wait till somebody leaves later in the day.

Follow the well maintained hiking trail that starts opposite of the parking lot. At the base of the summit there is small trail branching off. This is marked with green colored dots. The last section to the summit is marked with little stone pyramids.  I looped around the summit and returned on a well maintained fire service road passing a fire watch tower.

Carry plenty of water with you. You will pass the spring Fuente del Cedro that did have water in the middle of August(!), but I would not drink it untreated.
track_title: Montana del Cedro from a parking lot on TF-38

track_notes:
Start from Parking - Mirador de las Narices del Teide - on road or take the footpath.
The path leading up to the ridge is clearly visible and established with small rock walls.
Further on the ridge a path marked with stone cairns leads up the summit.
There is a well on the way (cave filled with water). Only drink it if you have a water filter (or similar). Birds bath in the water. Huge stone cairn on summit. Lots of space and great view to El Teide
